cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image segmentation using Active Shape Models. The use of a generalized least-squares approach and a weighting matrix also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The evaluation of the technique on X-ray images suggests that it could also belong to the Medical Imaging (cs.MS) category. Finally, the use of landmarks and contour-based segmentation techniques suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category.
